The impact of measurement errors on dietary pattern analysis: A simulation study based on dietary data from the China Multi-Ethnic Cohort (CMEC) Study.
Measurement errors could distort dietary patterns and attenuate the dietary pattern-disease association. The stability of dietary patterns under measurement errors differs when using PCFA and KCA.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Vitamin D supplementation in COPD patients with low serum vitamin D: a randomized controlled trial.
 Vitamin D supplementation did not reduce exacerbation rate in COPD patients with a vitamin D deficiency.
